    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>ruin, ruins, ruined</h1><h2>Definition:</h2><p>To “ruin” something means to spoil, destroy, or cause to be useless. The term “ruin” or “ruins” refers to the rubble and spoiled remains of something that has been destroyed.</p><ul><li><p>The prophet Zephaniah spoke about the day of God’s wrath as a “day of ruin” when the world will be judged and punished.</p></li><li><p>The book of Proverbs says that ruin and destruction await those who are ungodly.</p></li><li><p>Depending on the context, to “ruin” could be translated as to “destroy” or to “spoil” or to “make useless” or to “break.”</p></li><li><p>The term “ruin” or “ruins” could be translated as “rubble” or “broken-down buildings” or “destroyed city” or “devastation” or “brokenness” or “destruction,” depending on the context.</p></li></ul><p>(See also: <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25666\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">devastated</span>)</p><h2>Bible References:</h2><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:7-2Chr12:8\">2 Chronicles 12:7–8</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:25-2Kgs19:26\">2 Kings 19:25–26</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:16\">Acts 15:16</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:13-Isa23:14\">Isaiah 23:13–14</a></p></li></ul><h2>Word Data:</h2><ul><li><p>Strong’s: H0006, H1197, H1530, H1820, H1942, H2034, H2040, H2717, H2719, H2720, H2723, H2930, H3510, H3765, H3782, H3832, H4072, H4288, H4384, H4654, H4876, H4889, H5221, H5327, H5557, H5754, H5856, H7451, H7489, H7582, H7591, H7612, H7701, H7703, H7843, H8047, H8074, H8077, H8414, H8510, G26790, G26920, G36390, G44850</p></li></ul>",
